    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>9. Devonshire <hi rend="print">Street</hi> | Portland Place</placeName>
                    <date>Feb 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You gave me the enclosed charming photograph.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Now I am going to beg a great favour, which it is quite likely you may not wish to grant.— In my little book on Expression I wish to give a plate by the Heliotype process of 2 or 3 smiling faces. For this process the negative is required. Now sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> you object to <hi rend="underline">lending</hi> me the negative, with the permission to state that the Photograph was done by you.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>You must, of course, have not the slightest scruple in refusing me.— But if you grant this favour, could you send me the negative to above address by Delivery Co<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> <hi rend="underline">soon</hi>, as I want much to get the Heliotypes plates finished soon.—</p>
<p>Was the smile intentionally assumed? or taken when the sitter did not know what you were doing?</p>
<p>My dear Sir | yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
